  "prompt": "How can I retrieve saved messages in Snapchat that got deleted when person unfriended me?",
  "response": "Once someone unfriends you on Snapchat, any saved messages that were shared between you two typically become inaccessible. Snapchat's design prioritizes user privacy and ephemeral content, meaning conversations are generally temporary and can be deleted without recovery options. \n\nHere are a few suggestions:\n\n1. **Check Saved Messages Before Being Unfriended**:\n   Ensure you have saved important messages on your end before any risk of being unfriended.\n\n2. **Contact Snapchat Support**:\n   Although chances are slim, you may try contacting Snapchat support to inquire if there's any possible way to retrieve lost conversations.\n\n3. **Backup Important Data Regularly**:\n   For future instances, consider taking periodic screenshots of important conversations or using a note-keeping app to manually save crucial information.\n\nAlways keep in mind the importance of privacy and the transient nature of certain social media communications.",
